700130f-c.title: Bronx: 149th Street (East) - Anthony J. Griffin Place
700130f-c.text:
E. 149th Strect, north sidem east from Anthony J, Briffin
Place. At this point the street is above the New York
Central and'New Haven railroad tracks. The tall building
is the ten-story Terminal Building, near the northeast
corner of Park Avenue. View 2 shows the low buiding
at the northeast corner of Park Avenue. View 3 is east from
the Terminal Building.
P. L. Sperr  April 28, 1941
NO RERODUCTIONS  Views 1, 2, 3

700131f-a.title: Bronx: 149th Street (East) - Anthony J. Griffin Place
700131f-a.text:
(11 Nast 149th Street, north stde, west from Anthoney J. Griffin
Place to Grand Concourse, showing the Mott Haven auto wrecking
yard and an old diner.
(2) shows a closeup. Cn this side, there was later erected the
Bronx Central Annex Post Office.
P. L. Sperr  August 28, 1930
No Reproductions  Views 1,2
